# Anti-Duplication

Do not copy similar logic across files/functions. Extract shared helpers/services.

Priority duplication hotspots to prevent:
- Export success flow (history save, navigation to completion page)
- Frame extraction and compose orchestration
- Layout block mapping and transformation logic
- Repeated native bridge parameter assembly

Enforcement:
- If the same logic appears twice, refactor into one reusable function/service.
- Prefer small shared helpers over large copy-pasted branches.
- Keep one canonical implementation per workflow.

When refactoring:
- Preserve existing behavior and data contracts.
- Add concise inline comments only for non-obvious decisions.
